frus:attachment.p:
The bulletins of our brave generals might have contained useful information
                        for us. An intelligent officer, who notices what is occurring around him,
                        can give a correct account of it, and we should have had their reports.

M. Thiers said, “I think there is some exaggeration on the part of England;
                        the claim of Spain seems more reasonable; but our claim is certainly
                        exorbitant.”
